                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d26">
                <head>No. 26.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tree</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-01-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 3, 1887</date>. (Received January
                        17.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 185.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I understand that the newly-established wires
                    connecting Brussels with Paris by telephone were tried a day or two since, and
                    that the trials were perfectly successful. The line will be handed over to the
                    public use within a few days.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lambert Tree.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
